s a plural the les but it stays the same for groupsthings of either gender.";i:36;s:57:"Similarly you have a masculine a un and a feminine a une.";i:37;s:90:"In french it is very important to pay attention towards gender as we do in Hindi language.";i:38;s:62:"Like if I ask you what is the gender of truck or pen in Hindi.";i:39;s:86:"Feminine and neuter gender but in French we have two gender ie masculine and feminine.";i:40;s:66:"In french book pen are masculine whereas chair chalk are feminine.";i:41;s:26:"Posted by Unknown at 2331.";i:42;s:177:"Chair or chairperson policeman or policewoman by police officer spokesman by spokesperson stewardess by flight attendant headmaster or headmistress by director or principal etc.";i:43;s:75:"This gender-neutral trend has led to the disappearance of the older female.";i:44;s:187:"Theres no simple trick to knowing the gender of every single French noun other than looking in a dictionary but there are several categories of words that are always or usually masculine.";i:45;s:86:"Le calendrier is masculine as are all days of the week months of the year and seasons.";i:46;s:173:"How to learn the gender in French For native speakers it seems that the gender is learned during early childhood in a natural and unconscious way without posing any problem.";i:47;s:87:"But for non-native French students this is one of the most complicated thing to master.";i:48;s:33:"Feminine and masculine in French.";i:49;s:41:"Learning French grammar can be very hard.";i:50;s:82:"One thing that will definitely help you improve your French is to know the gender.";i:51;s:96:"Therefore the best way to keep genders straight is to always learn new words with their genders.";i:52;s:88:"When youre making flashcards or repeating French nouns aloud dont just say chaise chair.";i:53;s:124:"Make sure you say une chaise a chair or la chaise the chair so your brain gets used to that words gender from the beginning.";i:54;s:21:"But were not perfect.";i:55;s:32:"Add 